Question: How do you believe ACME should better support organizations and cultural leaders?

Response ID: resp_1962
Response Text: We have a unique opporunity to bring Austin's creative community together and focus on uplifting all of the amazing artistic work generated in this community. I would like to see theatre, dance, performance, and literary arts raised to the same level of awareness as music, film, and sports. We can not possibly attend all of the cultural events in Austin. ACME can help get the word out and cross promote all of the differents kinds of opportunities there are in Austin to experience art and culture. 

Our non-profit venues are struggling to stay open with the rising costs of taxes, rents, and utilities. We need to strengthen that infrastructure and make sure that the venues survive as they serve so many companies and artists. ACME needs to establish a venue fund to offer the kind of support that is received by ZACH and the Long Center for the many small venues, studios, theatre, and galleries that are run by non-profits. We will pay $40,000 back to the city for electricity and water this year.

